Cinnamon is Spayed, UTD on vaccines and tested negative for FIV/FeLV. Approx. DOB is July 15, 2016.Cinnamon is a sweet, laid back cat who likes quiet company, laser pointers, and treats. She was adopted as a kitten, then came back to NAR as an adult when her people didn't stay together. She will need a patient person to help her feel secure in her new home and allow her personality to shine.&nbsp;Cinnamon gets along with other mellow cats. She has never met dogs or children.&nbsp;
If you're interested in adopting&nbsp;Cinnamon&nbsp;please fill out an application at&nbsp;http://nar.rescuegroups.org.

I&rsquo;m Lucy! Born about March 2016, beautiful Autumn coloring. I am friendly and spunky! I have some resistance to using the litter but would love for you to sponsor me so I can continue being cared for at our wonderful shelter.&nbsp;I am spayed with updated shots and the volunteers take such good care of me here!&nbsp;

Interested in Volunteering?&nbsp;
Please visit our website to fill out a volunteer application:
http://bingosfoundation.org/wordpress/volunteer/

Meet Rosie! Rosie was adopted from the rescue as a kitten nine years ago and is now looking for a new home, through&nbsp;no fault of her own (members of Rosie&#39;s family have developed allergies).&nbsp;   

Rosie is a sweet cat who is friendly with adults but does not care for kids.&nbsp;She is skittish around children and would prefer an adult-only home, where she will be more comfortable. She has always been a solo cat and has lived fully indoors.&nbsp;She&nbsp;is spayed, negative for FIV/FeLV, and current on vaccines (Rabies, FVRCP, and feline leukemia). She is also current on parasite prevention.&nbsp;  

Rose&#39;s current owner says &quot; She is loyal and smart as a whip. She would fetch a string and bring it back to me like a dog. My sister was amazed. In the morning when I make my bed, I&rsquo;ll say, &#39;ok, Rose, you know the drill,&#39;&nbsp;and she immediately goes and sits at the end of the bed! Rose would be a wonderful companion to a couple with no kids and no pets, or a single person wanting a loyal and sweet buddy. She&rsquo;s not high energy and does not scratch everything up. In that way she is almost perfect for older people. &quot;   

If you are the right family for this lovely girl who is so deserving of a second chance,&nbsp;please apply by&nbsp;clicking on&nbsp;More About Rose&#39;s Rescue -&nbsp;you may fill out adoption application from there. Or, go to the Rose&#39;s Rescue website,&nbsp;www.rosesrescue.net, and click on Fees - Adoption Info - Online Application.&nbsp;Thank you for considering adoption - our adoptable cats can&#39;t wait to meet you!

FRED is a sweet and gentle boy, looking for a forever home with his sister, Ginger. These two have been together since they were found as kittens in a car engine back in 2022.&nbsp; Fred's shy yet, friendly demeanor makes him the perfect companion for cozy evenings. Once he feels safe with you, he loves to cuddle; offering comfort and affection to anyone who needs a friend. Fred and Ginger are inseparable, providing each other with support and love.
&nbsp;
These bonded siblings were recently surrendered to us through no fault of their own.&nbsp; They need a calm, quiet home with consistent, unconditional love.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
TEXT Anita to adopt Fred and Ginger:&nbsp; 407-460-2305.See the home page for adoption fee info:&nbsp; https://spaythestrays.rescuegroups.org/
